sectiondiv.p:
To customize the CSS to set an image to be displayed
          in a tile, follow these steps:

Make sure you set an id on the topic that you want the tile include an image.

Create a new CSS file that contains a rule that associates an image with a specific
              tile. The CSS file should have content that is similar to
              this:.wh_tile[data-id='growing-flowers']> div {
    background-image:url('resources/flower.png');
}

Use the Customizing WebHelp Output with a Custom CSS or the Create a WebHelp Responsive Skin method to pass the CSS file you just
              created to the transformation scenario.
